f(x)=\frac{x}{x-1}
f(x)=\frac{x}{x-1} = \frac{(x - 1) + 1}{x-1} = 1 + \frac 1{x-1}
(\dagger)
f'(x) = \frac{d}{dx}\left(\frac 1{(x-1)}\right) = \frac{d}{dx}(x - 1)^{-1} = -{(x - 1)^{-2}} = \frac{-1}{(x-1)^2}
f(x) = \frac{x}{x-1} = x(x-1)^{-1}.
f'(x) = (1)(x-1)^{-1} + x \cdot (-1)(x-1)^{-2} = \frac{x-1 - x}{(x-1)^2} = \frac{-1}{(x-1)^2}.
f(x)=\frac{x}{x-1}
f'(x)=\frac{(x-1)\frac{d}{dx}(x) -[ x\frac{d}{dx}(x-1)]}{(x-1)^2}
\frac{d}{dx}(x) = 1
\frac{d}{dx}(x-1) = 1
f'(x) = \frac{(x-1)(1) - x(1)}{(x-1)^2}
\frac{(x-1) - x}{(x-1)^2} = \frac{x - 1 - x}{(x-1)^2} = -\frac{1}{(x-1)^2}
